    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-06-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 527.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 505, of the
                    13th ultimo, I inclose copy of No. 120<note n="l" xml:id="d531fnl">Not
                        printed.</note>, of the 10th instant, from our commercial agent at Sagua la
                    Grande, reporting that Messrs. William A. and Louis M. Glean are still held on
                    parole, subject to military jurisdiction, and that the nature of the charge of
                    which they are accused has not been made known to them.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
